This is a textbook case of **coverage-touching tests** — every method is called, none are meaningfully verified. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 Critical — No Assertions At All (tests can never fail)

These tests execute code but assert nothing. A method could return garbage or corrupt state and the test stays green.

**1. `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)**
Calls `AddProduct` but never verifies the product was persisted.
```csharp
// Fix: verify round-trip
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(result);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", result.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result.Price);
```

**2. `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32)**
Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price actually changed. A no-op `Save()` would pass.
```csharp
// Fix: assert the new price
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

**3. `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38)**
Calls `RemoveProduct` but never checks the product is gone. `Delete` could be a no-op.
```csharp
// Fix: assert product is removed
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

**4. `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)**
Captures `count` into a local variable and discards it. Doesn't even call `Assert.IsNotNull`.
```csharp
// Fix: assert expected count
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(1, _catalog.GetProductCount());
```

**5. `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68)**
Applies a 10% discount but never checks that any price changed. The core discount math is completely unverified.
```csharp
// Fix: assert discounted prices
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
```

**6. `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 84)**
Imports a CSV row but never checks the product was created or parsed correctly. Malformed parsing would pass.
```csharp
// Fix: verify imported product
_catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
var product = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(product);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", product.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, product.Price);
